      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match COU operating envelope within stated tolerances; temperature, hematocrit, and flow rate deviations must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro test conditions matched 3 of 5 COU operating points. Hematocrit deviation of ±4% from target at two operating points was not propagated into uncertainty budget. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or U95) must show prediction within acceptance band at all COU operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions within ±25% at 3 of 5 operating points; two high-speed operating points show errors of 31% and 38%. Acceptance band of ±15% not met. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI must be directly the clinical decision variable (absolute NIH) with no surrogate substitution; sensitivity of clinical outcome to QoI must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the direct clinical QoI. However, the model predicts volume-averaged NIH rather than the spatially resolved shear-exposure distribution required for MRL 5 absolute prediction. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must span the full COU operating envelope including worst-case high-speed, low-flow conditions; device geometry must be identical to COU device.",
      "rationale": "Validation used FDA generic pump geometry, not the specific VAD device geometry. Operating envelope coverage is partial (3 of 5 points). Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, round-off error, and time-stepping error must each be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to GCI.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (achieved level 2 documentation); round-off and time-stepping error contributions not formally quantified. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
