      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation protocol with independent review; evidence that boundary condition setup, turbulence model selection, and post-processing scripts were independently verified.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. Boundary condition scripts not version-controlled. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive law must include sensitivity analysis across plausible model form alternatives at COU conditions.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected without systematic comparison to LES or RSM alternatives at VAD Reynolds numbers. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law not evaluated against Arora or Faghih models. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be traceable to post-revision characterisation data; Monte Carlo UQ must propagate input uncertainties through to NIH QoI.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated but the blood rheology and viscosity inputs (primary fluid properties) are drawn from a dataset with vintage 2025-10-01, predating the model revision date of 2026-02-15. The revised model incorporates updated impeller geometry that alters near-wall shear profiles; re-characterisation of fluid properties under the new geometry is planned for Q2 2026 but has not been completed. Input uncertainty propagation therefore reflects the prior model configuration. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Blood analogue samples must be characterised for lot-to-lot variability; hematocrit and plasma viscosity must be measured pre- and post-test.",
      "rationale": "Single blood analogue lot used across all experiments; no lot-to-lot variability characterisation performed. Pre/post hematocrit measurements incomplete. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
